                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Pyongyang joins Facebook
          LAURA ROBERTS                              
	Aug. 21: North Korea appears to have joined the social networking site Facebook after its Twitter account was blocked by South Korea under the countrys security laws.        
	The account, opened on Thursday night under the Korean username uriminzokkiri, meaning on our own as a nation, an official at South Koreas Communications Standards Commission said yesterday.        
	It appeared hours after the commission blocked North Koreas 1-week-old Twitter account from being accessed in the South for containing information that is illegal under South Korean security laws, the official said.        
	North Koreas government-run website, Uriminzokkiri, announced last week that it has a Twitter account and a YouTube channel which was created in July.                            THE DAILY TELEGRAPH                                                                                                                                                  
